text:
I don’t really know where to start but I am a long stay guest at this hotel and I thought I should list the issues I have faced with his hotel from day 1.

1. Dried blood on bathrobe;
2. Toenail clippings in bathrobe;
3. The lack of mopping or cleaning the floor although this is supposed to be a serviced apartment;
4. Washing of plates and crockery and utensils with just water pressure and no soap;
5. Nobody cleans the tubs so there was thick orange and yellow gunk in it;
6. Getting bitten by mosquitoes 4 days in a row at night;
7. Fruit flies/ flies in the toilet - vent has a nest somewhere;
8. Contaminated water from the water dispenser for 2 months;
9. Water dispenser doesn’t turn off so floods the apartment which already has a slippery marble floor;
10. Moldy cabinets because cabinet right next to bathroom, mold fell into cups and plates in the cabinet (asked the staff to fix it but they just ended up being in the room for 20 minutes whilst I was in the shower just hanging out whilst leaving the door to the room open);
11. Emailed the GM regarding these problems but never got a response and instead saw this note slipped under my door - see below. So the GM was sick for almost 2 weeks then because that’s how long I didn’t get a response for;
12. Washing machine gives persistent error and doesn’t clean;
13. Shoe print on pillow;
14. I had to throw away a box of cotton buds because the housekeeping decided it would be a great idea to tip them all upside down and have them fall on the floor which is never cleaned.

If you want peace of mind, I would suggest not staying in this serviced apartment/ hotel because their idea of 5 star standards seem to be very different from an objective average guest. Also, service seems to be a take it or leave it thing with them because nobody really cares if you tell them the apartment is falling apart.

For starters, they offered free contaminated water as a gesture of goodwill when I told them about the blood and toenails in my bathrobe that wasn’t mine. And then left me hanging with the dirty contaminated water for 2 months and after the dispensers were changed and the water still contaminated as you can see in the picture below, I asked if it could be the barrel of water attached to the dispenser or a rubber tubing somewhere, the assistant GM basically said oh we’ve already done our best so there’s nothing more we can do and looked peeved to be hearing a complaint.

As I’ve mentioned, standards are on a whole new level here. 

Perhaps the management should try and get their staff to attend hospitality school because basic manners like apologizing for the lack of standards also do not exist in terms of decorum in relation to certain staff. 

As for the mold which I’ve informed them about, I basically have to put up with it and not utilize that specific cupboard or the crockery because they would take 5 days to fix it but also in the meanwhile, the rest of the other rooms are not available to be moved into.  

Wonderful stay, perfect. 

On another note, the rest of the ground staff are friendly. Also, the location of the apartment is great.
